===Etymology===
(1125–75) {{etyl|enm}} ''[[fruit#Middle English|fruit]]'' "fruits and vegetables" from {{etyl|fro}} ''[[fruit#Old French|fruit]]'' from {{etyl|la}} ''[[fructus|fructus]]'' "enjoyment, proceeds, profits, produce, income", a derivative of {{etyl|la}} ''[[frui]]'' "to have the benefit of, to use, to enjoy" from {{proto|Indo-European|bhrug-|to make use of, to have enjoyment of}}; cognate with Modern {{etyl|de|-}} ''[[brauchen]]'' "to use", {{en}} ''[[brook]]'' "to tolerate". Displaced native {{enm}} ''[[ovet#Middle English|ovet]]'' "fruit" (from {{ang}} ''[[ofett#Old English|ofett]]'' "fruit"), {{enm}} ''[[wastum#Middle English|wastum, wastom]]'' "fruit, growth" (from {{ang}} ''[[wæstm#Old English|wæstm]]'' "growth, produce, increase, fruit"), {{enm}} ''[[blede#Middle English|blede]]'' "fruit, flower, offspring" (from {{ang}} ''[[bled#Old English|blēd]]'' "fruit, flower").

