====Usage notes====
* In the botanical and figurative senses, {{term||fruit|lang=en}} is usually treated as uncountable:
*: ''a bowl of '''fruit'''''; ''eat plenty of '''fruit'''''; ''the tree provides '''fruit'''.''
* {{term|fruits|Fruits|lang=en}} is also sometimes used as the plural in the botanical sense:
*: ''berries, achenes, and nuts are all '''fruits'''''; ''the '''fruits''' of this plant split into two parts.''
* When {{term||fruit|lang=en}} is treated as uncountable in the botanical sense, {{term||a piece of fruit|lang=en}} is often used as a singulative.
* In senses other than the botanical or figurative ones derived from the botanical sense, the plural is {{term|fruits|lang=en}}.

